# File Naming Convention

All file names must use kebab-case (hyphen-separated lowercase words).

Examples:
- ✅ `game-tree-builder.ts`
- ✅ `tree-utils.ts`
- ✅ `node-editor.vue`
- ❌ `gameTreeBuilder.ts` (camelCase)
- ❌ `GameTreeBuilder.ts` (PascalCase)
- ❌ `game_tree_builder.ts` (snake_case)

This rule applies to:
- TypeScript files (`.ts`, `.tsx`)
- JavaScript files (`.js`, `.jsx`)
- Vue files (`.vue`)
- All other source code files

Exception: Configuration files that follow their own conventions (e.g., `package.json`, `tsconfig.json`) are exempt from this rule.
